There&#39;s an interesting preface to the 2000 edition to Choshu in the Meiji Restoration, giving some of the ideas Craig would either change or elaborate if he were writing now. It&#39;s too long to precis here. He also gives several books written since, which you probably already know: Ones I haven&#39;t read but would like to get hold of are Kelly: Deference and Defiance in 19th c Japan 1985. Koschmann; The Mito Ideology 1987. Baxter The Meiji Unification through the lens of Ishikawa Prefecture 1994. Shiba Goro Remembering Aizu. 1999

Mito in the Meiji Restoration - that would be the most enthralling, I reckon. Maybe some Phd student is working on it in Mito right now...

The MR is like a jigsaw puzzle, so many bits to fit in and so much happening. Craig says, &#39;it was in fact the great cultural and institutional divide between the old Japan and the new.&#39;

